alternatives.transcript: two year old female elementary school teacher who presented today with a two month history of shortness of breath and fatigue she's also been experiencing palpitations and presyncope and was referred to us after visiting her primary care physician her vital signs are heart rate of a hundred and ten a blood pressure of one thirty six over ninety nine respiratory rate is twenty o2 saturation is ninety two percent and temperature is ninety eight point six she has a history of hypertension sarcoidosis which is taking ten milligrams of lisinopril and ten milligrams of prednisone she has had a previous cardiac catheterization with no signs of obstructive coronary artery disease her family history includes the sudden death of her mother at four years old and the death of her father fifty nine from a myocardial infarction her diet is fairly balanced and she has she used to exercise regularly until she starts experiencing the shortness of breath she does not use tobacco alcohol or any illicit drugs and her caffeine intake is one cup per day one cup of coffee she has experienced an eight pound weight gain over the past few weeks along with orthotonia and swelling in her legs i admitted her for continued cardiac monitoring with daily checks or daily weight checks oxygen and for that to be maintained over a ninety six percent saturation and dvt prophylaxis i increased her dosage of prednisone to and kept her lisinopril dosage the same she will remain on a low sodium diet and is allowed activity or movement with assistance i added a hundred fifty milligrams of amiodarone and forty milligrams of furosemide to help with the swelling and ordered cmp to monitor her potassium levels i've also gotten consultations to interventional cardiology for an aicd placement as well as radiology for an fdg pest scan
